The paper discusses the use of data motifs to create proxy benchmarks for big data and AI workloads. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including cs.AR (Architecture), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.SY (Systems and Control). However, since the focus is on architecture and performance simulation, cs.AR is the most likely category. cs.AI is also likely due to the mention of AI workloads, while cs.DC and cs.DB are relevant due to the focus on big data. cs.SY is less likely but still possible due to the mention of micro-architecture performance data.
